WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:44.128 --> 00:46.587
Greetings, my friend.

00:46.672 --> 00:50.049
You are interested in the unknown,

00:50.134 --> 00:53.678
the mysterious, the unexplainable.

00:53.762 --> 00:56.681
That is why you are here.

00:56.765 --> 00:58.933
And now, for the first time,

00:59.017 --> 01:02.645
we are bringing you the full story
of what happened.

01:02.730 --> 01:05.272
We are giving you all the evidence

01:05.357 --> 01:08.818
based only on the secret testimony
of the miserable souls

01:08.902 --> 01:12.405
who survived this terrifying ordeal.

01:12.489 --> 01:15.408
The incidents, places.

01:15.492 --> 01:18.995
My friend, we cannot keep this
a secret any longer.

01:19.288 --> 01:22.081
Can your heart stand the shocking facts

01:22.166 --> 01:24.125
of the true story

01:24.209 --> 01:27.336
of Edward D. Wood, Jr?

05:12.562 --> 05:16.148
It's 8:15.
We can't hold the curtain any longer.

05:16.233 --> 05:19.402
Cripes, what am I gonna tell the cast?
It's press night and there's no press!

05:20.779 --> 05:23.990
- Do you believe in ghosts?
- Nah, Tommy.

05:24.074 --> 05:26.033
That's just kiddie spook stories.

05:26.118 --> 05:30.121
Once you're dead, you stay dead.

05:30.247 --> 05:31.622
I don't know, Bill.

05:32.249 --> 05:36.127
Out on that battlefield today,
I saw this woman dressed in white

05:36.211 --> 05:38.713
floating above the dunes.

05:38.922 --> 05:43.300
Maybe it was just fatigue
or maybe it's the indignities of war.

05:43.385 --> 05:45.469
Or maybe it's somethin' else.

05:48.682 --> 05:51.600
Hey, I think I see somethin'.

05:57.774 --> 06:01.610
I offer you mortals the bird of peace

06:01.820 --> 06:04.321
so that you may change your ways

06:04.448 --> 06:06.782
and end this destruction.

06:13.790 --> 06:15.833
What a show! Everyone was terrific.

06:15.917 --> 06:18.878
Paul, your second act monologue
actually gave me the chills.

06:18.962 --> 06:20.212
Oh, thanks, Eddie.

06:20.297 --> 06:22.006
I got the early edition,
hot off the presses!

06:22.090 --> 06:24.008
This is the big moment.

06:34.311 --> 06:37.396
Oh, what does that old queen know?

06:37.481 --> 06:39.482
She didn't even show.

06:41.985 --> 06:44.612
Sent her copy boy to do the dirty work.

06:44.696 --> 06:50.367
- Screw you, Miss Crowley.
- Do I really have a face like a horse?

06:50.452 --> 06:52.578
What does "ostentatious" mean?

06:52.662 --> 06:55.247
Hey, it's not that bad.
You can't concentrate on the negative.

06:55.332 --> 06:57.458
Look, he's got some nice things
to say here.

06:57.542 --> 07:00.377
"The soldiers' costumes are very realistic."
That's positive!

07:00.462 --> 07:03.798
- Rave of the century.
- Well, I've seen a lot worse reviews.

07:03.882 --> 07:06.967
I've seen reviews where they didn't
even mention the costumes.

07:07.052 --> 07:09.970
Like that last Francis the Mule picture.
It got terrible notices.

07:10.055 --> 07:12.014
- Huge hit!
- Lines around the block.

07:12.099 --> 07:15.893
That's right. Don't take it too seriously.
We're all doing great work.

07:15.977 --> 07:18.229
- Do you really think so?
- Absolutely.

07:19.856 --> 07:22.233
Honey, what if I'm wrong?

07:22.317 --> 07:26.529
- What if I just don't got it?
- Ed, it was only one review.

07:26.613 --> 07:30.241
Orson Welles was only 26
when he made <i>Citizen Kane.</i>

07:30.534 --> 07:32.284
I'm already 30.

07:33.703 --> 07:35.996
Ed, you're still young.

07:36.081 --> 07:38.958
This is the time in your life
when you're supposed to be struggling.

07:39.042 --> 07:43.212
I know. But I'm scared it's not going
to get any better than this.

07:46.341 --> 07:49.969
Oh, I hate having to wake up this early.

07:56.226 --> 07:58.769
Gosh, where's my pink sweater?

08:00.105 --> 08:02.898
I can never seem to find
my clothes anymore.

08:08.864 --> 08:12.950
Hey, big shot! Get off your ass
and get this over to the executive building.

08:13.034 --> 08:17.413
- Sure thing, Mr. Kravitz.
- Hey, Charlie, come here.

08:17.497 --> 08:20.708
What did I tell ya about watering these plants, eh?
I want some water on 'em!

08:20.792 --> 08:23.419
Don't sprinkle the damn things!
Soak 'em!

08:33.096 --> 08:35.097
Hi.

08:35.182 --> 08:38.058
All right, people, settle.
And action!

08:47.819 --> 08:50.487
Wow! Look at these camels!

08:50.572 --> 08:52.489
These are real camels!

08:54.034 --> 08:57.244
- Gosh, where'd they get real camels?
- Hey, you!

08:57.329 --> 08:59.830
Move it outta here, huh?

09:04.461 --> 09:09.256
Hey, Eddie! Come in here.
I got some great new stuff to show you.

09:20.268 --> 09:22.603
This is fantastic.
What are you gonna do with it?

09:22.687 --> 09:25.314
Probably file it away
and never see it again.

09:25.398 --> 09:26.690
Ah, it's such a waste.

09:30.528 --> 09:31.612
Why, if I had half the chance,

09:31.696 --> 09:33.822
I could make an entire movie
using this stock footage.

09:36.952 --> 09:40.454
The story opens on these
mysterious explosions.

09:40.538 --> 09:43.582
Nobody knows what's causing them,
but it's upsetting all the buffalo.

09:43.667 --> 09:46.627
So the military are called in
to solve the mystery.

09:46.711 --> 09:48.504
You forgot the octopus.

09:48.588 --> 09:51.090
No, no. I'm saving that
for my big underwater climax.

09:55.303 --> 09:56.845
Hello.

09:56.930 --> 09:59.890
They say he was a girl
trapped in a man's body.

09:59.975 --> 10:01.976
I bet it hurt when
they cut his thing off.

10:03.853 --> 10:05.646
What are you ladies gabbin' about?

10:05.855 --> 10:07.439
You know that Christine Jorgensen freak?

10:07.524 --> 10:10.109
- It's...
- He... She... in <i>Variety.</i>

10:10.193 --> 10:12.653
Some producer's makin' a biopic.

10:13.738 --> 10:16.407
Really? I didn't read that story.

10:18.660 --> 10:21.495
Yes, I've got Mr. Edward Wood
on the line.

10:21.579 --> 10:23.539
Could you please hold?

10:26.001 --> 10:29.211
Mr. Weiss? Ed Wood here.

10:29.296 --> 10:30.921
Listen, I heard about your new project

10:31.006 --> 10:33.507
and I was curious
if you'd signed a director yet.

10:33.591 --> 10:35.551
Oh, you haven't!

10:35.635 --> 10:38.137
Well, if we could get together,
I could explain to you

10:38.221 --> 10:42.016
why I'm more qualified to direct this
than anyone else in town.

10:43.435 --> 10:47.021
Well, I'd rather not go into that
over the phone.

10:47.105 --> 10:49.273
All right. Great!

10:49.357 --> 10:52.234
I'll see you then. Bye!

10:53.111 --> 10:54.361
Eddie, I don't understand.

10:54.446 --> 10:57.948
Why are you the most qualified director
for the Christine Jorgensen story?

10:58.074 --> 11:00.576
Oh, it's just hogwash, hon.
I had to get into the door somehow.

11:21.723 --> 11:23.640
No, I love you like a brother.

11:23.725 --> 11:27.269
No, no, no. No, no, no.
That's a falsehood!

11:28.938 --> 11:30.856
Come in!

11:30.940 --> 11:34.068
Look, when I said
you could have the western territories,

11:34.152 --> 11:36.320
I didn't mean all 11 states!

11:36.613 --> 11:40.240
I meant California, Oregon,
and what's that one on top?

11:40.325 --> 11:42.284
Washington, yeah, yeah!

11:42.369 --> 11:44.536
Oh, really?

11:44.621 --> 11:46.622
Well, screw you!

11:48.041 --> 11:49.500
Hi. Can I help you?

11:49.584 --> 11:50.584
Yes. I'm Ed Wood.

11:50.668 --> 11:52.628
I'm here about directing
the Christine Jorgensen picture.

11:53.712 --> 11:55.422
Well, a couple of things have changed.

11:55.507 --> 11:57.883
It ain't gonna be
the Christine Jorgensen story no more.

11:57.967 --> 12:00.636
Goddamn <i>Variety</i> had to print the story
before I got the rights.

12:00.720 --> 12:03.847
- Now that bitch is asking for the sky.
- Ah, you're not gonna make the movie.

12:03.973 --> 12:06.350
No, of course I'm gonna make the picture.

12:06.434 --> 12:09.228
I already presold Alabama and Oklahoma.

12:09.312 --> 12:12.481
Those repressed Okies,
they go for that twisted, perverted stuff.

12:13.274 --> 12:15.484
We'll just do it without the she-male.
We'll fictionalize it.

12:15.568 --> 12:19.863
- Is there a script?
- Fuck no. But, there's a poster.

12:22.534 --> 12:25.327
It opens in nine weeks in Tulsa.

12:25.578 --> 12:27.913
Well, Mr. Weiss, look no further.
I'm your man.

12:27.997 --> 12:31.917
I work fast and I'm a deal.
I write and direct. And I'm good.

12:32.001 --> 12:33.293
I just did a play in Hollywood

12:33.378 --> 12:35.712
and Victor Crowley himself
praised its realism.

12:36.005 --> 12:38.674
There's about 500 guys in this town
that can say the same thing.

12:38.758 --> 12:42.344
On the phone you said you had
some special qualifications?

12:47.684 --> 12:49.643
Mr. Weiss

12:50.728 --> 12:52.980
I have never told anyone

12:53.064 --> 12:55.232
what I'm about to tell you.

12:55.316 --> 12:57.693
But I really want this job.

13:00.780 --> 13:03.323
I like to dress in women's clothing.

13:05.535 --> 13:06.660
You're a fruit?

13:06.744 --> 13:08.537
No, not at all. I love women.

13:08.621 --> 13:10.581
Wearing their clothes
makes me feel closer to them.

13:11.124 --> 13:15.002
- You're not a fruit.
- No, I'm all man. I even fought in WWII.

13:15.086 --> 13:17.254
Of course, I was wearing
women's undergarments under my uniform.

13:18.006 --> 13:20.090
Ya got to be kidding me.

13:20.175 --> 13:23.385
Confidentially, I even paratrooped
wearing a brassiere and panties.

13:23.803 --> 13:26.805
I tell ya, I wasn't scared of being killed,
but I was terrified of getting wounded

13:26.890 --> 13:28.432
and having the medics discover my secret.

13:29.726 --> 13:31.810
So you think this qualifies you
to make my movie?

13:31.895 --> 13:33.645
Yes!

13:34.355 --> 13:36.732
I know what it's like to live with a secret

13:36.816 --> 13:38.400
and worry about what people
are gonna think of ya.

13:40.236 --> 13:43.405
My girlfriend still doesn't know
why her sweaters are always stretched out.

13:45.033 --> 13:48.535
Ed, you seem like a nice kid.
Look around you.

13:48.620 --> 13:52.331
I don't hire directors with burning desires
to tell their stories.

13:52.415 --> 13:54.416
I make movies like <i>Chained Girls.</i>

13:54.501 --> 13:55.792
I need someone with experience

13:55.877 --> 13:58.128
who can shoot a film in four days
and make me a profit.

13:58.254 --> 14:00.756
I'm sorry. That's all that matters.

14:04.761 --> 14:07.387
Can I get you anything else, kid?

14:56.020 --> 14:59.398
Too constrictive!
I can't even fold my arms.

14:59.482 --> 15:01.775
Gee, Mr. Lugosi,
I've never had any complaints.

15:01.985 --> 15:05.237
This is the most uncomfortable coffin
I've ever been in.

15:05.321 --> 15:08.907
Your selection is quite shoddy.
You're wasting my time!

15:10.827 --> 15:11.868
Mr. Lugosi?

15:11.953 --> 15:13.954
I told you I don't want
any of your goddamn coffins!

15:14.038 --> 15:16.582
No, no! I don't work here.

15:16.666 --> 15:19.751
- Then who are you? What do you want?
- I don't want anything.

15:19.836 --> 15:23.213
I'm just a really big, big fan.
I've seen all your movies.

15:27.719 --> 15:30.095
Mr. Lugosi, why are you buying a coffin?

15:30.179 --> 15:31.513
I'm planning on dying soon.

15:31.598 --> 15:33.265
- No!
- Yes!

15:33.349 --> 15:35.434
I'm embarking on another bus
and truck tour of <i>Dracula.</i>

15:35.518 --> 15:38.437
Twelve cities in 10 days,
if that's conceivable.

15:38.521 --> 15:42.024
Do you know that I saw you perform <i>Dracula</i>
in Poughkeepsie in 1938?

15:42.108 --> 15:43.775
That was a terrible production.

15:43.860 --> 15:46.445
- Renfield was a drunk!
- I thought it was great.

15:46.529 --> 15:50.115
You know, you're much scarier in real life
than you are in the movie.

15:50.199 --> 15:52.117
Thank you.

15:52.201 --> 15:54.661
I even waited outside to get your autograph,
but you never came out.

15:54.746 --> 15:57.831
Well, I apologize. When I play Dracula,
I put myself into a trance.

15:57.915 --> 16:00.459
It takes me much time to reemerge.

16:01.794 --> 16:05.130
Oh, there's my bus.
Shit, where is my transfer?

16:05.214 --> 16:08.133
- Say, don't you have a car?
- I refuse to drive in this country.

16:08.217 --> 16:10.218
Too many madmen.

16:11.137 --> 16:13.472
I've got a car.

16:18.895 --> 16:22.272
Boy, Mr. Lugosi,
you must lead such an exciting life.

16:22.357 --> 16:26.735
- When is your next picture coming out?
- I have no next picture.

16:26.819 --> 16:28.153
You gotta be jokin'.

16:28.237 --> 16:31.031
A great star like you,
you must have dozens of 'em lined up.

16:31.115 --> 16:33.492
Back in the old days, yes.

16:33.743 --> 16:36.495
But now, no one gives two fucks for Bela.

16:36.579 --> 16:39.956
- But you're a big star.
- No more.

16:40.083 --> 16:42.125
I haven't worked in four years.

16:43.628 --> 16:47.798
This business, this town,
it chews you up, then spits you out.

16:47.882 --> 16:52.260
I'm just an ex-bogeyman.
Make a right.

17:06.150 --> 17:08.944
They don't want
the classic horror films anymore.

17:10.279 --> 17:13.531
Today, it's all giant bugs.

17:13.616 --> 17:15.909
Giant spiders, giant grasshoppers.

17:15.992 --> 17:17.786
Who would believe such nonsense?

17:18.287 --> 17:22.749
The old ones were much spookier,
they had castles and full moons.

17:22.834 --> 17:24.626
They were mythic.

17:24.836 --> 17:27.212
- They had a poetry to them.
- Yes.

17:27.296 --> 17:30.215
And you know what else? The women...

17:30.299 --> 17:34.386
The women prefer the traditional monsters.

17:34.470 --> 17:36.388
The women. Huh.

17:36.472 --> 17:40.642
The pure horror,
it both repels and attracts them.

17:40.727 --> 17:43.353
Because in their collective unconsciousness,

17:43.646 --> 17:45.897
they have the agony of childbirth.

17:45.982 --> 17:49.651
The blood... The blood is horror.

17:51.237 --> 17:53.155
You know, I never thought of that.

17:55.283 --> 17:57.200
Take my word for it.

17:57.285 --> 17:59.828
If you want to make out
with a young lady

17:59.912 --> 18:01.798
you take her to see <i>Dracula.</i>

18:10.506 --> 18:12.424
Eh, what a mess.

18:12.508 --> 18:15.427
My wife of 20 years left me last month.

18:15.511 --> 18:17.004
I'm not much of a housekeeper.

18:17.889 --> 18:20.932
All right, I'm coming.
I'll feed you, my darlings.

18:21.017 --> 18:22.058
I'd better get going.

18:22.268 --> 18:25.812
But perhaps we could get together
again some time, Mr. Lugosi.

18:26.898 --> 18:28.815
Certainly.

18:28.900 --> 18:32.486
But now, the children of the night
are calling me.

18:34.071 --> 18:35.023
Uh...

18:36.783 --> 18:38.700
- Good day.
- Good day.

18:42.038 --> 18:45.081
Sweetie, you won't believe it.
I've got incredible news.

18:45.208 --> 18:47.793
- You got the job!
- No, I didn't get the job.

18:47.877 --> 18:51.505
- But something better happened.
- Better than not getting the job.

18:51.589 --> 18:54.257
Yes! I met a movie star.

18:54.550 --> 18:58.136
- Somebody really big.
- Who? Robert Taylor?

18:58.221 --> 19:01.348
No. A horror movie star.

19:01.432 --> 19:03.892
- Boris Karloff?
- Close.

19:03.976 --> 19:05.018
The other one.

19:06.562 --> 19:09.481
You met Basil Rathbone!

19:09.565 --> 19:12.818
Oh, to heck with you.
I met Bela Lugosi.

19:12.902 --> 19:17.405
- Why, I thought he was dead.
- No, he's very much alive.

19:17.490 --> 19:18.824
Well,

19:18.908 --> 19:20.033
sort of.

19:21.077 --> 19:25.330
He's old and frail, but he's still Bela Lugosi
and he's really nice.

19:25.414 --> 19:27.791
I can't even remember the last time
I saw him in a picture.

19:27.875 --> 19:29.125
It's a shame.

19:29.210 --> 19:31.586
He's such a great actor
and no one uses him anymore.

19:31.712 --> 19:34.506
- So, did you get his autograph?
- No, it wasn't like that at all.

19:34.590 --> 19:38.927
It was just the two of us and we were talking.
He treated me like a friend.

19:39.053 --> 19:41.555
- Yeah, well, he's a bum.
- No, he's not.

19:41.639 --> 19:44.099
Do you have any idea how much money
he made for this studio?

19:44.183 --> 19:46.142
<i>Dracula, The Black Cat, The Raven.</i>

19:46.227 --> 19:48.353
Yeah? Well, now he's a junkie.
He don't deserve to work.

19:48.437 --> 19:52.440
- That is not true!
- He's so great, you hire him.

19:53.708 --> 19:55.652
Yeah, well, I would if I could.

19:57.196 --> 19:58.655
Trick or treat!

19:58.739 --> 20:00.949
The house looks like
they have lots of kids.

20:25.641 --> 20:29.019
<i>Oh, those eyes.
He gives me the willies.</i>

20:29.103 --> 20:32.063
Uh, I hate it when she interrupts the picture.

20:32.148 --> 20:35.066
She doesn't show 'em
the proper respect.

20:35.151 --> 20:37.110
I think she's a honey.

20:38.487 --> 20:40.572
Look at those jugs.

20:40.656 --> 20:43.199
<i>But he stood me up at the restaurant.</i>

20:43.284 --> 20:45.452
<i>I guess I shouldn't have picked
a steak house.</i>

20:47.496 --> 20:50.457
<i>And then I went out with the Wolf Man.
What an evening. </i>

20:50.541 --> 20:52.626
<i>I didn't know whether
to kiss him good night...</i>

20:52.710 --> 20:57.422
Vampira, you will come under my spell.

20:59.842 --> 21:03.345
You will be my slave of love.

21:03.429 --> 21:06.306
My gosh, Bela! How do you do that?

21:06.390 --> 21:09.434
You must be double-jointed.

21:09.518 --> 21:11.853
And you must be Hungarian.

21:13.856 --> 21:17.067
Vampira, look at me.

21:17.151 --> 21:20.111
Look into my eyes.

21:20.196 --> 21:22.864
<i>You're watching our Halloween movie,
White Zombie</i>

21:23.115 --> 21:26.284
<i>starring Bela Lugosi,
John Harron, Madge Bellamy,</i>

21:26.369 --> 21:28.995
<i>and a bunch of other people
I've never heard of.</i>

21:33.668 --> 21:35.710
I'm very tired.

21:36.837 --> 21:39.089
I need to take my medicine.

21:39.882 --> 21:42.217
- Do you want me to get it for you?
- No.

21:42.468 --> 21:44.719
Thank you, Eddie.
I'll be all right.

22:14.791 --> 22:16.584
Oh, shit.

22:32.075 --> 22:33.977
I feel much better!

22:35.061 --> 22:37.272
Children! I love children!

22:43.112 --> 22:45.448
Trick or treat!

22:47.700 --> 22:50.702
Aren't you scared, little boy?

22:50.786 --> 22:54.372
I'm going to drink your blood.

22:54.457 --> 22:56.458
You're not a real vampire.

22:56.959 --> 22:59.711
Those teeth don't frighten me.

23:01.380 --> 23:03.423
How about these?

23:05.134 --> 23:08.470
Hey, how'd you do that?

23:08.554 --> 23:12.307
Dentures. Lost my pearlies in the war.

23:12.808 --> 23:17.020
So, what was the important news
you couldn't tell me on the phone, again?

23:17.146 --> 23:18.938
I started thinking about
what you were saying

23:19.023 --> 23:20.899
about how your movies
need to make a profit.

23:20.983 --> 23:24.903
What is the one thing, if you put it
in a movie, it'll be successful?

23:24.987 --> 23:27.530
- Tits.
- No, better than that. A star.

23:27.782 --> 23:30.992
Kid, you must have me confused
with David Selznick.

23:31.077 --> 23:33.411
I don't make major motion pictures,
I make crap.

23:33.496 --> 23:37.248
Yes! But if you take that crap and put
a star in it, then you've got something.

23:37.333 --> 23:40.251
- Yeah. Crap with a star.
- No, something better!

23:40.336 --> 23:42.128
Something impressive.

23:42.379 --> 23:45.173
Maybe the biggest money-maker
you've ever had.

23:46.257 --> 23:47.550
Fine, all right.

23:47.635 --> 23:49.969
You may be right,
but it doesn't frickin' matter.

23:50.054 --> 23:52.472
I can't afford a star,
so what are we even talkin' about?

23:52.556 --> 23:55.850
All right. What if I told you
you could have a star for $1,000?

23:56.310 --> 23:58.269
Who?

24:03.359 --> 24:05.985
- Lugosi?
- Yes! Lugosi!

24:06.070 --> 24:07.445
Isn't he dead?

24:07.530 --> 24:09.614
No, he's not dead.
He lives in Baldwin Hills.

