45:20.802 --> 45:22.761
Morphine.

45:23.429 --> 45:25.472
With a Demerol chaser.

45:28.309 --> 45:33.021
Oh, Eddie. Eddie, I'm so broke.

45:34.273 --> 45:36.274
I don't know what I'm going to do.

45:40.655 --> 45:42.489
Don't worry, Bela.

45:44.283 --> 45:46.827
I won't let you down.

45:49.789 --> 45:52.124
Mr. Feldman? Ed Wood.

45:52.208 --> 45:55.252
Yeah, listen, I haven't been able to get through,
so I just showed up.

45:55.336 --> 45:57.295
Yeah! Right out front.

45:57.380 --> 45:59.756
So, we gonna be working together?

46:01.342 --> 46:04.845
Really? Worst film you ever saw.

46:04.929 --> 46:08.140
Well, my next one will be better.

46:08.224 --> 46:11.184
Hello. Hello.

46:13.436 --> 46:14.938
I'm no good.

46:15.022 --> 46:17.941
Oh, Ed, it was just one man's opinion.

46:18.025 --> 46:21.528
Bela needs a job.
I can't even get a film going.

46:21.612 --> 46:24.448
Of course I can't.
I made the worst movie of all time.

46:24.532 --> 46:26.450
Oh, that's ridiculous.

46:27.660 --> 46:30.579
All I wanna do is tell stories.

46:30.663 --> 46:33.498
The things that I find interesting.

46:33.583 --> 46:36.793
Well, maybe you're not
studio kind of material.

46:36.878 --> 46:39.838
Maybe you just need
to raise the money yourself.

46:42.592 --> 46:45.218
The movie is called <i>Bride Of The Atom.</i>

46:45.303 --> 46:48.305
It will star Bela Lugosi.

46:48.389 --> 46:50.974
There are quarter shares
available at $15,000 each.

46:51.350 --> 46:54.060
Yes, that's right.
The Bela Lugosi.

46:55.104 --> 46:57.481
He's still alive.

46:57.565 --> 47:01.193
Huh? Is he available Friday night?

47:01.277 --> 47:03.987
Well, gee, I suppose so. Why?

47:05.071 --> 47:08.074
"Greetings, I am the Count."

47:08.159 --> 47:11.286
"Greetings, I am Slick Slomopavitz,
Seeker of Adventure.

47:11.370 --> 47:15.081
"Audience laughs, applauds.
'Say, that's a kooky place to sleep.'"

47:15.291 --> 47:19.419
- "It is my home."
- "Oh, tract housing, huh? Laugh."

47:19.545 --> 47:21.172
"You need a new real estate agent."

47:22.256 --> 47:24.174
"I beg to differ.

47:24.258 --> 47:27.928
"This casket incap... incarpertate..."

47:28.012 --> 47:29.930
No, Bela, that's "incorporates."

47:30.014 --> 47:32.766
Look, why don't you just say,
"This casket has..."

47:33.059 --> 47:36.228
How do they expect a Hungarian
to pronounce this dialogue?

47:36.312 --> 47:39.231
This live television is madness!

47:39.315 --> 47:41.608
Furthermore, I predict

47:41.692 --> 47:44.986
by April 19, 1970,

47:45.071 --> 47:49.032
I predict men will have colonized Mars.

47:49.116 --> 47:51.284
Millions of people will live there.

47:51.953 --> 47:55.038
Wow! Ain't that somethin'?

47:58.459 --> 48:01.836
And now we take you
to a castle in Transylvania.

48:01.921 --> 48:06.925
Watch out.
The landlord's a real pain in the neck.

48:24.527 --> 48:27.904
Greetings! I am the Count!

48:27.989 --> 48:31.575
Greetings, pal!
I'm Slick Slomopavitz, Seeker of Adventure!

48:32.952 --> 48:35.245
Hey, what a kooky place to sleep.

48:35.329 --> 48:37.831
Kind of reminds me of my house.
What a dump!

48:37.957 --> 48:40.834
Some places got a Murphy bed,
this place got a Murphy shower.

48:40.918 --> 48:43.420
I still don't know
where to hang the towels.

48:43.504 --> 48:45.422
I beg to differ.

48:45.506 --> 48:50.760
Beg to differ? A bloodsucker, right?
I'm talkin' about my towels.

48:55.016 --> 48:58.518
Greetings! I am the Count.

49:03.816 --> 49:04.934
Damn!

49:11.824 --> 49:15.535
A bum is what he is.
I told you we should've got Karloff!

49:19.040 --> 49:20.957
Ah, don't worry about it, Bela.
You're better than all this.

49:21.042 --> 49:22.542
I never said I could ad-lib.

49:22.627 --> 49:24.836
Forget it! We'll make our own movie
and you'll be a big star again.

49:26.380 --> 49:30.884
Mr. Lugosi, it is an unparalleled
privilege to meet you, sir.

49:30.968 --> 49:34.346
Allow me to introduce myself.
I am Criswell.

49:34.430 --> 49:36.389
It's a pleasure.

49:36.474 --> 49:40.560
Ah, cheer up. Don't lose heart
over what happened tonight.

49:40.645 --> 49:45.065
I predict your next project
will be an outstanding success!

49:45.691 --> 49:47.567
Wow!

49:47.902 --> 49:49.736
And who may you be?

49:49.820 --> 49:51.864
Edward D. Wood, Jr.

49:52.948 --> 49:56.368
- The director of <i>Glen Or Glenda?</i>
- How'd you know?

49:56.452 --> 49:59.788
I am Criswell. I know all.

50:09.924 --> 50:12.592
And bingo!
Thank you, thank you, thank you.

50:12.718 --> 50:16.680
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
Bring me two more Beefeater martinis.

50:16.764 --> 50:18.682
Ed, another whiskey.

50:18.766 --> 50:20.684
Dagmar, a rum and coke?

50:20.768 --> 50:22.852
Moustapha and King are Chablis.

50:22.937 --> 50:25.980
Bela, would you like a wine?

50:26.315 --> 50:29.484
No. I never drink wine.

50:34.824 --> 50:39.202
Say, Cris, how'd you know we'd be
living on Mars by 1970?

50:39.286 --> 50:42.205
- I guessed.
- Really?

50:42.289 --> 50:44.249
I made it up.

50:44.333 --> 50:46.292
It's horse shit.

50:47.503 --> 50:50.422
Eddie, there's no such thing
as a psychic.

50:50.506 --> 50:54.467
People believe my folderol
because I wear a black tuxedo.

50:54.552 --> 50:57.554
- It's that easy?
- Eddie, we're in show biz.

50:57.638 --> 51:01.057
It's all about razzle-dazzle, appearances.

51:01.142 --> 51:04.894
If you look good and you talk well,
people will swallow anything.

51:13.362 --> 51:17.532
We are going to have the most
terrifying monster ever seen on film.

51:17.616 --> 51:21.911
A ghastly creature created
from an atomic mutation!

51:21.996 --> 51:23.913
I don't like scary movies.

51:23.998 --> 51:25.915
I like the ones with love stories.

51:26.000 --> 51:28.918
That's just what this movie is:
a heartbreaking romance.

51:29.003 --> 51:30.962
You're quite a specimen.

51:31.046 --> 51:33.882
- And you're going to be in the picture?
- Yeah. I play Lobo.

51:33.966 --> 51:38.470
I predict <i>Bride Of The Atom</i> will be
the biggest moneymaker of all time.

51:38.554 --> 51:42.515
And this is lovely starlet Dolores Fuller,
who will play Janet Lawton.

51:42.600 --> 51:45.935
My pleasure, ma'am.
Now, how much will this picture cost?

51:46.020 --> 51:49.439
Well, in a normal studio it'd be
about a million bucks

51:49.523 --> 51:52.484
with all their wasteful overhead
and fancy offices.

51:52.568 --> 51:55.028
But we're more efficient,
so we could bring it in at about 70 grand.

51:56.280 --> 51:58.990
Oh. Well, I shall certainly consider it.

51:59.074 --> 52:02.368
- Well, goodbye.
- Good night, Ed. Keep in touch.

52:02.453 --> 52:04.412
Goodbye.

52:07.249 --> 52:09.209
Well, Eddie, how'd we do?

52:09.293 --> 52:11.085
We didn't make a nickel.

52:12.046 --> 52:14.964
I cannot believe I'm in Hollywood.

52:15.049 --> 52:17.842
You know, Daddy didn't want me
to move out here.

52:19.094 --> 52:22.388
Ma'am, your bill comes to $2.20.

52:22.473 --> 52:25.433
Oh. Uh, okay. I hope you don't mind

52:25.518 --> 52:28.645
but all I have is a fifty.
I just came from my banker's.

52:28.729 --> 52:30.688
- That's all right.
- Thank you.

52:37.863 --> 52:40.240
Excuse me. You just moved here?

52:40.449 --> 52:43.576
Yes. Hollywood is, oh, so exciting.

52:43.661 --> 52:44.711
Isn't it?

52:45.663 --> 52:48.164
Pleased to make your acquaintance.
I'm Loretta King.

52:48.249 --> 52:50.416
Edward D. Wood, Jr.

52:50.501 --> 52:52.919
Hi. Would you like some water?

52:53.003 --> 52:54.003
No!

52:54.088 --> 52:56.506
No water. No liquids.

52:56.590 --> 52:58.716
I'm terribly allergic to them.

53:00.678 --> 53:03.596
You know, I work in Hollywood.
I'm a producer.

53:03.681 --> 53:05.598
Really? Wow!

53:05.683 --> 53:08.226
I would love to be involved in that.

53:08.310 --> 53:11.271
Is that right?
Well, maybe I can help you out.

53:11.355 --> 53:14.607
Have you ever thought about
investing in a motion picture?

53:14.859 --> 53:16.860
Perhaps a small amount of money.

53:16.944 --> 53:18.820
How much do your motion pictures cost?

53:19.071 --> 53:22.740
Well, my new one, I think,
would be about $60,000.

53:22.825 --> 53:26.870
That's all? That seems very reasonable
for an entire picture.

53:29.957 --> 53:32.917
Would you like to

53:33.002 --> 53:36.379
- have a look at the photoplay?
- Oh, sure.

53:38.507 --> 53:40.425
Oh, my.

53:40.509 --> 53:43.052
This is very interesting.

53:43.137 --> 53:46.055
Say, do you think it would be possible

53:46.140 --> 53:48.349
for me to maybe play one of these parts?

53:48.434 --> 53:51.394
Oh, you want to be an actress, too.
Well, of course.

53:51.478 --> 53:55.231
There's a couple of parts I can think of right now
that you might be perfect for.

53:55.316 --> 54:00.111
There's the secretary in the newspaper office,
the file clerk...

54:00.195 --> 54:02.906
Hmm. Those sound kind of small.

54:04.033 --> 54:06.701
Here's one that looks good, Janet Lawton.

54:08.370 --> 54:11.331
I'd sure like to play her.

54:11.415 --> 54:13.458
- Janet Lawton.
- Yes.

54:13.542 --> 54:16.502
Janet Lawton is clearly the part to play.

54:18.964 --> 54:21.674
Can't you just see me in the part?

54:27.389 --> 54:29.349
Yes!

54:29.433 --> 54:31.351
You'd be perfect.

54:33.646 --> 54:35.563
You bastard!

54:35.648 --> 54:39.776
You two-timing, dress-wearing son of a bitch!

54:39.860 --> 54:42.820
Honey, it was the only way
I could get the movie made!

54:42.905 --> 54:44.822
Who do you think's been paying the rent?

54:44.907 --> 54:48.868
Who's been helping you type your scripts
and do all your grunt work?

54:48.953 --> 54:50.495
I am sorry!
What did you want me to say?

54:50.579 --> 54:52.038
You were supposed to say,

54:52.122 --> 54:56.918
"No. I wrote that part
for my girlfriend Dolores!"

54:58.295 --> 55:01.756
Snowball, there are plenty of other parts.

55:01.840 --> 55:04.425
Like what?

55:05.928 --> 55:07.680
The secretary, the file clerk.

55:08.764 --> 55:11.724
You asshole!

55:14.895 --> 55:18.314
This is gonna be Bela's laboratory,
so it should be real impressive

55:18.399 --> 55:20.775
just like one of those
"Mad Scientist" movies.

55:21.026 --> 55:24.153
I want test tubes, beakers and one
of those electrical things that buzzes.

55:24.238 --> 55:26.990
- You mean a Tesla coil?
- Fine. Whatever. Hop to it!

55:27.074 --> 55:29.033
Right! Right.

55:30.786 --> 55:32.745
- Eddie?
- Yes?

55:32.830 --> 55:36.666
- Which dress do you like better?
- Hmm. I don't know.

55:36.750 --> 55:41.129
Say, Bill, which dress works better for you,
the red one or the green one?

55:41.213 --> 55:44.173
- Which one is the red one?
- What do you mean?

55:44.258 --> 55:47.635
I mean, I can't see the difference,
I'm color blind.

55:47.720 --> 55:49.887
But I kinda like the dark gray one.

55:52.099 --> 55:56.644
At Universal, we used to shoot
one or two scenes a day.

55:56.729 --> 55:59.731
But Eddie can knock off 20, 30.

55:59.815 --> 56:02.442
- He's incredible!
- And action!

56:06.697 --> 56:10.241
Okay, you're Dr. Eric Vornoff

56:10.325 --> 56:12.243
and you're upset.

56:12.327 --> 56:13.786
You've worked very hard
on this experiment

56:13.871 --> 56:16.539
and you don't want to see it fail.

56:16.623 --> 56:18.541
No, you're not that upset.

56:18.625 --> 56:22.003
You wanna keep moving.
You wanna go through that door.

56:25.841 --> 56:27.800
And cut! Beautiful.

56:27.885 --> 56:30.470
Print it.
Let's move immediately to scene 52.

56:30.554 --> 56:32.472
- Tor, you in place?
- Yeah.

56:32.556 --> 56:34.849
- Great. Roll camera!
- Rolling. Slate.

56:35.100 --> 56:36.394
Cue rainstorm.

56:37.978 --> 56:39.896
And action, Tor.

56:43.025 --> 56:46.152
Okay. You're Lobo.

56:46.236 --> 56:48.154
You're upset.

56:48.238 --> 56:52.200
You've worked very hard
helping Dr. Vornoff with this experiment.

56:52.284 --> 56:55.203
You don't wanna see it fail.

56:55.287 --> 56:57.246
No, no. You're not that upset.

56:57.331 --> 57:00.291
You wanna keep moving.
You've got to get through that door.

57:06.423 --> 57:08.174
And cut! Perfect!

57:08.425 --> 57:11.385
- Print it. Let's move on.
- Don't you wanna do another take, Ed?

57:11.470 --> 57:14.430
Looks like big baldy had a little trouble
gettin' through the door.

57:14.515 --> 57:16.474
No, it's fine. It's real.

57:16.642 --> 57:20.853
You know, in actuality, Lobo would have
to struggle with that problem every day.

57:21.188 --> 57:25.108
All right, people, let's get ready.
Actors! I must have my actors!

57:25.192 --> 57:26.442
There you are.

57:26.527 --> 57:29.278
Loretta, Tor, I wanna explain this scene,
it's a little complicated, but...

57:29.363 --> 57:31.815
Bela, you'll be sitting there. Okay?

57:32.699 --> 57:34.617
I'm not getting near that goddamn thing.

57:34.701 --> 57:36.953
One of them burned me
on <i>The Return Of Chandu.</i>

57:37.037 --> 57:38.704
All right.

57:39.164 --> 57:41.791
- Then you'll be sitting there.
- Good.

57:41.875 --> 57:44.168
Great. All right, gang, here's the scene.

57:44.253 --> 57:47.630
Loretta, you're in a trance,
you glide in and get on the operating table.

57:47.714 --> 57:50.925
Now, Tor, you're supposed to tie her down,
but you have an angora fetish

57:51.009 --> 57:54.137
and when you rub that swatch of angora,
it makes you refuse.

57:54.221 --> 57:58.182
So then Bela has to discipline you.
All right? Great! Let's do it!

58:00.018 --> 58:01.936
Action!

58:07.401 --> 58:09.944
Strap her to the table.

58:12.447 --> 58:14.824
Do as I command you!

58:16.702 --> 58:20.037
I'll teach you to disobey me!

58:20.122 --> 58:22.081
You will obey!

58:22.791 --> 58:24.134
Strap her in!

58:24.918 --> 58:27.920
Strap her in! I command you!

58:28.005 --> 58:30.923
- Wood! Your check bounced.
- I'll get you the money later.

58:31.008 --> 58:33.593
- No, I need it now.
- I'll teach you to disobey me!

58:33.677 --> 58:35.636
Cut!

58:36.138 --> 58:39.307
I am terribly sorry to bother you
while you're shooting

58:39.391 --> 58:42.351
but the guy that owns the stage
needs his money.

58:42.436 --> 58:45.771
Well, then, you should pay him,
shouldn't you?

58:45.856 --> 58:48.232
Yes. Exactly.

58:53.947 --> 58:55.907
I kind of need it now.

58:58.994 --> 59:02.455
What are you looking at me
like that for?

59:02.539 --> 59:05.708
I already gave you my three hundred.

59:05.792 --> 59:07.710
Right.

59:07.794 --> 59:10.463
And now I need the other sixty thousand.

59:10.672 --> 59:13.299
What other sixty thousand?

59:15.177 --> 59:18.971
The other sixty thousand
you said you'd give to me.

59:19.306 --> 59:21.515
You misunderstood, Eddie.

59:21.600 --> 59:25.228
I gave you everything I have in the world,
three hundred dollars.

59:41.954 --> 59:44.914
Well, here we go again.

59:44.998 --> 59:47.375
Let me tell ya, ya can't lose.

59:47.459 --> 59:50.628
It's scary. And if you don't like that,
it's romantic.

59:50.712 --> 59:53.673
Bela Lugosi will portray Dr. Eric Vornoff.

59:59.680 --> 01:00:03.391
And lovely, lovely, lovely
ingénue Loretta King

01:00:03.642 --> 01:00:06.102
is reporter Janet Lawton.

01:00:06.186 --> 01:00:09.188
- I don't know. Lugosi looks pretty old.
- Huh?

01:00:10.691 --> 01:00:12.692
Which role does Vampira play?

01:00:12.776 --> 01:00:15.528
Vampira? Why do you ask?

01:00:15.612 --> 01:00:17.863
She's standing right over there.

01:00:20.701 --> 01:00:23.160
Well, she plays...

01:00:25.580 --> 01:00:27.665
Excuse me one minute.

01:00:30.001 --> 01:00:31.127
Pardon me. Miss Vampira?

01:00:31.211 --> 01:00:34.171
- Yes?
- You don't know me, but I'm Ed Wood.

01:00:34.256 --> 01:00:37.633
I'm a film producer and I'm currently in production
on a science fiction piece

01:00:37.718 --> 01:00:40.094
with Bela Lugosi
and Swedish wrestler Tor Johnson.

01:00:40.178 --> 01:00:42.221
I don't understand.
Do you want my autograph?

01:00:43.390 --> 01:00:45.433
No.

01:00:45.517 --> 01:00:48.227
No, I think my film is perfect for you.

01:00:48.562 --> 01:00:50.646
You want me to show it
on my TV programme.

01:00:50.731 --> 01:00:52.315
I have nothing to do with that.

01:00:52.399 --> 01:00:54.150
You should call the station manager
at Channel 7.

01:00:54.234 --> 01:00:55.318
No, no. No, no, no, no.

01:00:55.402 --> 01:00:59.488
I don't want you to show the movie,
I want you to be in it. Let me explain.

01:00:59.573 --> 01:01:02.491
We started shooting,
but after three days we got shut down.

01:01:02.576 --> 01:01:04.994
Now we're having a backers party
to raise some more money.

01:01:05.078 --> 01:01:06.370
So I thought perhaps
you'd like to come over

01:01:06.455 --> 01:01:08.497
just to say "howdy"
to some of the backers.

01:01:08.582 --> 01:01:11.459
Look, I'm with some friends
and we're about to eat.

01:01:11.835 --> 01:01:13.753
Please! It would just take one second.

01:01:13.837 --> 01:01:15.463
Come over and meet the backers.

01:01:15.547 --> 01:01:17.673
There is a really nice dentist from Oxnard.

01:01:17.758 --> 01:01:20.301
Look, buddy, I've got real offers
from real studios.

01:01:20.385 --> 01:01:23.262
I don't need to blow some dentist for a part.
Forget it.

01:01:25.223 --> 01:01:27.350
Miss Vampira!

01:01:27.434 --> 01:01:29.894
- Please.
- Oh! Let's go.

01:01:31.480 --> 01:01:34.899
I'm getting a bad feeling about this.
Let's get out of here.

01:01:34.983 --> 01:01:37.068
Yeah, I think you're right.

01:01:37.152 --> 01:01:41.280
Thank you, folks, for comin' tonight,
but we better go.

01:01:41.782 --> 01:01:45.159
And then Dr. Vornoff falls into the pit

01:01:45.243 --> 01:01:48.371
and his own octopus attacks and eats him.

01:01:48.455 --> 01:01:49.831
The end.

01:01:51.625 --> 01:01:54.293
- Well, that's quite a story.
- Yes.

01:01:55.462 --> 01:01:58.047
So, uh, you made the movie

01:01:58.298 --> 01:02:00.716
and now you wanna make it again?

01:02:00.801 --> 01:02:02.676
No.

01:02:02.761 --> 01:02:06.722
We shot 10 minutes of the movie,
and now we're looking for completion funds.

01:02:06.807 --> 01:02:08.808
Oh, son, you're too vague.

01:02:10.718 --> 01:02:11.769
Billy Bob!

01:02:13.021 --> 01:02:15.815
You're cuttin' 'em too lean.

01:02:16.024 --> 01:02:18.067
Mr. McCoy.

01:02:19.569 --> 01:02:20.986
How can I make you happy?

01:02:23.365 --> 01:02:25.199
Okay.

01:02:25.492 --> 01:02:27.076
Two things.

01:02:27.160 --> 01:02:32.415
Number one: I want the movie
to end with a big explosion.

01:02:34.501 --> 01:02:36.502
Sky full of smoke.

01:02:38.255 --> 01:02:40.172
Yes.

01:02:40.257 --> 01:02:43.342
But it ends with Dr. Vornoff
falling into the pit.

01:02:43.427 --> 01:02:45.761
Not anymore.

01:02:46.346 --> 01:02:47.972
Number two:

01:02:48.056 --> 01:02:49.640
I got a son.

01:02:50.517 --> 01:02:53.519
He's a little slow, but a good boy.

01:02:55.105 --> 01:02:58.983
And somethin' tells me
he'd make a helluva leadin' man.

01:03:04.197 --> 01:03:05.364
Sounds perfect.

01:03:05.824 --> 01:03:07.491
This is unbelievable.

01:03:07.576 --> 01:03:10.411
I woulda bet a million bucks
that Ed wouldn't finish this picture.

01:03:10.495 --> 01:03:13.414
Yeah, well, it ain't finished yet, kid.
Anything can happen.

