01:28:34.685 --> 01:28:38.020
But I'll give you everything I've got,
a few hundred dollars.

01:28:38.105 --> 01:28:42.525
That won't even begin to cover it.
He's gonna have to leave.

01:28:46.822 --> 01:28:50.032
Bela? Bela, wake up.

01:28:51.910 --> 01:28:54.161
I've got some great news.

01:28:54.246 --> 01:28:56.789
The doctor says you're all better,
you can go home now.

01:28:58.625 --> 01:29:00.084
Really?

01:29:00.919 --> 01:29:02.628
I don't feel so great.

01:29:03.005 --> 01:29:06.590
No? Well, you look just peachy.

01:29:07.342 --> 01:29:09.510
And, uh, the tests came back fine.

01:29:09.594 --> 01:29:12.555
Come on, let's get up.

01:29:13.598 --> 01:29:15.808
Here we go.

01:29:15.892 --> 01:29:19.103
Attaboy. Good.

01:29:26.403 --> 01:29:28.404
Eddie,

01:29:28.488 --> 01:29:31.615
I want to make another picture.

01:29:31.700 --> 01:29:34.618
When are we going to make another picture?

01:29:34.745 --> 01:29:38.289
Oh... Soon, Bela. Very soon.

01:29:46.131 --> 01:29:47.966
This is so exciting.

01:29:49.051 --> 01:29:51.052
Another production.

01:29:51.136 --> 01:29:53.095
Isn't it?

01:29:53.180 --> 01:29:57.266
So, Eddie, shouldn't we
have a sound crew?

01:29:57.684 --> 01:30:00.686
Uh, no, no, because this
is just second unit stuff.

01:30:00.771 --> 01:30:03.814
We're gonna do the main footage later.
All right?

01:30:03.940 --> 01:30:05.775
So, what's this scene about?

01:30:06.902 --> 01:30:07.943
Um...

01:30:09.071 --> 01:30:11.322
You're a very important
and respected man.

01:30:11.615 --> 01:30:14.200
And you're leaving your house,
you're in a hurry.

01:30:14.284 --> 01:30:17.453
You're on your way to
a big social brouhaha. Okay?

01:30:17.746 --> 01:30:21.248
Eddie. What if I'm not in so big a hurry?

01:30:21.333 --> 01:30:24.251
What if I take a moment to slow down,

01:30:24.336 --> 01:30:26.754
to savor the beauty of life,

01:30:26.838 --> 01:30:30.758
to smell a budding flower?

01:30:30.842 --> 01:30:33.761
That's great. That is great.

01:30:33.845 --> 01:30:36.013
Let's do a take. Okay?

01:30:39.142 --> 01:30:40.976
Ed, I'm really busy.

01:30:41.061 --> 01:30:42.269
What do you want now?

01:30:42.354 --> 01:30:44.396
I was calling to see
if you'd like to attend

01:30:44.481 --> 01:30:47.024
the world premiere of my new movie,
<i>Bride Of The Monster.</i>

01:30:47.109 --> 01:30:48.859
Didn't you just make one
called <i>Bride Of The Atom?</i>

01:30:49.277 --> 01:30:50.444
Yes, it's the same film.

01:30:50.529 --> 01:30:52.905
But the distributor wanted a punchier title.

01:30:52.989 --> 01:30:54.490
Come on, it's gonna be a big event,

01:30:54.574 --> 01:30:57.034
Bela, Tor and Cris are coming.
You'll have fun!

01:30:59.729 --> 01:31:00.955
I can't see.

01:31:01.039 --> 01:31:03.207
These contact lenses are hurting.

01:31:03.291 --> 01:31:05.543
My eyes are killin' me.

01:31:05.794 --> 01:31:07.545
Don't worry. We're almost there.

01:31:15.061 --> 01:31:16.054
Hi.

01:31:16.638 --> 01:31:20.641
Right in there. Thank God you're here.
They're tearing up the place.

01:31:22.018 --> 01:31:24.103
Come on, come on.

01:31:24.187 --> 01:31:26.105
Come on, this way.

01:31:29.141 --> 01:31:30.276
Come on!

01:31:30.360 --> 01:31:32.319
Come on!

01:31:32.404 --> 01:31:34.613
I've never been to a movie premiere before!

01:31:46.585 --> 01:31:48.794
Well, go knock 'em dead.

01:32:03.685 --> 01:32:05.769
<i>At the stroke of midnight,</i>

01:32:06.062 --> 01:32:08.397
<i>the witching hour,</i>

01:32:08.481 --> 01:32:11.025
<i>the ghouls arise</i>

01:32:11.109 --> 01:32:12.985
<i>from the dead!</i>

01:32:21.411 --> 01:32:24.371
- Hey, Vampira, how 'bout a little love!
