01:33:35.944 --> 01:33:37.903
Did you see that kid
grab Vampira's boobies?

01:33:37.988 --> 01:33:42.283
I envied him.
Hell, I envied you, too.

01:33:42.367 --> 01:33:47.037
A girlfriend who would jump
in front of a car like that.

01:33:47.122 --> 01:33:49.790
Yes, she is quite something.

01:33:49.874 --> 01:33:52.042
None of my wives would have.

01:33:55.547 --> 01:33:59.300
Eddie, I want to thank you.

01:34:00.510 --> 01:34:03.304
These last few days have been

01:34:03.388 --> 01:34:05.306
a good time.

01:34:06.808 --> 01:34:08.726
You know, I just...

01:34:08.810 --> 01:34:10.937
I just wish you coulda seen the movie.

01:34:12.022 --> 01:34:13.939
No problem.

01:34:14.024 --> 01:34:16.233
I know it by heart.

01:34:23.116 --> 01:34:25.659
"Home.

01:34:25.744 --> 01:34:28.746
"I have no home.

01:34:29.581 --> 01:34:31.582
"Hunted.

01:34:31.708 --> 01:34:34.084
"Despised.

01:34:34.336 --> 01:34:36.670
"Living like an animal.

01:34:36.755 --> 01:34:40.007
"The jungle is my home.

01:34:40.091 --> 01:34:42.009
"But I shall show the world

01:34:42.093 --> 01:34:45.346
"that I can be its master!

01:34:45.430 --> 01:34:49.266
"I shall perfect my own race of people.

01:34:49.351 --> 01:34:51.769
"A race of atomic supermen

01:34:51.853 --> 01:34:54.355
"that will conquer the world!"

01:34:57.942 --> 01:35:01.487
Uh, Mr. Lugosi, could I have
your autograph, please?

01:35:01.571 --> 01:35:03.864
- Certainly.
- Why, that was incredible.

01:35:03.948 --> 01:35:06.200
I mean, you're just
as great as you ever were.

01:35:06.284 --> 01:35:08.202
Better.

01:35:08.286 --> 01:35:11.372
I am 74, but I don't know it.

01:35:11.456 --> 01:35:13.415
When the brain is young

01:35:13.500 --> 01:35:17.086
the spirit is still vigorous.

01:35:17.170 --> 01:35:19.963
Like a young man.

01:35:22.300 --> 01:35:24.385
"And left the planet Mars

01:35:24.469 --> 01:35:26.220
"never to return again."

01:35:27.146 --> 01:35:28.380
"The end."

01:35:33.853 --> 01:35:35.646
Wood Productions.

01:36:32.495 --> 01:36:35.873
Hey, whose crazy idea was it
to bury him in the cape?

01:36:35.957 --> 01:36:39.460
I heard it was in the will,
it was how he wanted to be remembered.

01:37:15.079 --> 01:37:17.080
Could you run it again?

01:37:29.928 --> 01:37:32.846
- Mr. Wood.
- Huh?

01:37:32.931 --> 01:37:35.849
Mr. Wood, this is Mr. Reynolds,
your landlord.

01:37:35.934 --> 01:37:38.185
Could you please open up?

01:37:38.269 --> 01:37:40.270
One minute.

01:37:42.065 --> 01:37:43.148
Yes?

01:37:43.233 --> 01:37:47.402
Uh, Mr. Wood, you have bounced
your third and final rent check.

01:37:48.530 --> 01:37:50.447
I'm terribly sorry.

01:37:50.532 --> 01:37:52.866
My stockbroker must've transferred
the wrong account.

01:37:52.951 --> 01:37:54.910
Come on in.
I'll write you another check.

01:38:00.207 --> 01:38:02.167
I see you're in the picture business.

01:38:02.252 --> 01:38:06.338
- Yes.
- I'm interested in the picture business.

01:38:06.422 --> 01:38:07.839
My associates and I,

01:38:07.924 --> 01:38:10.759
we wish to produce
a series of uplifting religious films

01:38:10.843 --> 01:38:13.011
about the apostles.

01:38:13.096 --> 01:38:16.181
But unfortunately,
we don't have enough money.

01:38:16.432 --> 01:38:18.183
Well, raising money's tough.

01:38:18.268 --> 01:38:21.228
No, our church has enough money
for one film.

01:38:21.312 --> 01:38:24.231
We just don't have enough for all 12.

01:38:26.150 --> 01:38:28.485
Well, you know what you do?

01:38:28.611 --> 01:38:31.405
You produce a film in
a commercially-proven genre

01:38:31.489 --> 01:38:32.489
and then after it's a hit,

01:38:32.574 --> 01:38:34.992
you take the profits from that
and make the 12 apostles movies.

01:38:35.243 --> 01:38:37.786
