01:38:43.668 --> 01:38:46.003
<i>Grave Robbers From Outer Space.</i>

01:38:46.129 --> 01:38:48.422
Money in the bank.

01:38:48.506 --> 01:38:50.465
Grave robbers from what?

01:38:50.550 --> 01:38:54.428
From outer space. It's science fiction.
Very big with the kids.

01:38:54.512 --> 01:38:56.013
If you make this picture,

01:38:56.097 --> 01:38:58.432
you'll have enough money
to finance 100 religious films

01:38:58.516 --> 01:39:00.851
and pay my back rent with the profits.

01:39:00.935 --> 01:39:05.188
I don't know.
This is all a lot to absorb.

01:39:05.481 --> 01:39:07.232
It's a guaranteed blockbuster.

01:39:09.319 --> 01:39:12.779
I understand this science fiction
is very popular, but,

01:39:12.864 --> 01:39:15.949
don't the big hits always have big stars?

01:39:16.034 --> 01:39:19.995
- Well, we have a big star, Bela Lugosi.
- Bela Lugosi...

01:39:20.079 --> 01:39:21.872
Oh, I thought he passed on.

01:39:23.416 --> 01:39:26.043
Yes. Yes, he did.

01:39:26.336 --> 01:39:27.961
But...

01:39:30.715 --> 01:39:34.926
- I've got the last footage he ever shot.
- Doesn't look like very much.

01:39:38.514 --> 01:39:42.684
Mr. Reynolds, this is the acorn
that will grow a great oak.

01:39:43.728 --> 01:39:45.103
I'll just get a double to finish his scenes

01:39:45.188 --> 01:39:47.856
and we'll release it
as Bela Lugosi's final film.

01:39:48.191 --> 01:39:50.484
Bunny? We're makin' another movie.

01:39:50.568 --> 01:39:53.820
Yes, I got the Baptist Church of Beverly Hills
