01:42:43.533 --> 01:42:45.909
Let's hear you call
Boris Karloff a cocksucker.

01:42:48.663 --> 01:42:51.456
We want these Baptists
to like us. Please.

01:42:51.707 --> 01:42:54.584
<i>Alleluia</i>

01:42:54.836 --> 01:42:57.087
Brothers and sisters,

01:42:57.213 --> 01:43:01.174
we reach now in the service
a joyous point

01:43:01.259 --> 01:43:05.345
because we are going to bear witness
to the baptism of our new members.

01:43:05.429 --> 01:43:07.931
Why couldn't we do this in the church?

01:43:08.015 --> 01:43:10.684
Because Brother Tor couldn't fit
in the sacred tub.

01:43:11.185 --> 01:43:13.770
Welcome to the fold, brother.

01:43:15.189 --> 01:43:18.400
Do you accept Jesus Christ
as your personal savior?

01:43:18.484 --> 01:43:19.526
Yes!

01:43:19.610 --> 01:43:23.196
In the name of the Father,
the Son and the Holy Ghost.

01:43:23.281 --> 01:43:24.407
Amen.

01:43:28.703 --> 01:43:31.663
Welcome to the fold, brother. Welcome.

01:43:33.958 --> 01:43:35.959
Praise the Lord, brother.

01:43:40.006 --> 01:43:42.966
Do you reject Satan and all his evils?

01:43:43.050 --> 01:43:44.968
Sure.

01:43:45.052 --> 01:43:48.430
In the name of the Father,
the Son and the Holy Ghost.

01:43:54.854 --> 01:43:57.564
Praise the Lord, friends!

01:43:57.648 --> 01:44:00.609
- Do you repent for all your sins?
- I do.

01:44:00.693 --> 01:44:03.236
How do you do it? How do you get
all your friends to get baptized

01:44:03.321 --> 01:44:05.322
just so you can make a monster movie?

01:44:05.406 --> 01:44:07.073
It's not a monster movie.

01:44:07.158 --> 01:44:09.492
- It's a supernatural thriller.
- Come to Jesus, brother!

01:44:25.843 --> 01:44:28.178
I can't believe this.

01:44:43.361 --> 01:44:45.612
- Ed, what am I gonna do here?
- What do you mean?

01:44:45.696 --> 01:44:47.238
He has no hair.

01:44:47.323 --> 01:44:50.408
Gee, I never noticed that.
Put a wig on him!

01:44:51.160 --> 01:44:54.537
Before we start shooting, Mr. Wood,
we have a few questions.

01:44:54.789 --> 01:44:58.375
Yes. The script contains
numerous references to grave robbing.

01:44:58.459 --> 01:45:00.335
Now, we find the concept

01:45:00.419 --> 01:45:03.046
of digging up consecrated ground
to be highly offensive.

01:45:03.130 --> 01:45:04.714
It is blasphemy.

01:45:04.799 --> 01:45:07.342
What are you talking about?
It's the premise of the movie.

01:45:07.426 --> 01:45:09.302
It's the title of the movie,
for Christ's sakes!

01:45:09.387 --> 01:45:10.804
Mr. Wood!

01:45:10.888 --> 01:45:12.806
Yes, about that title.

01:45:12.890 --> 01:45:15.225
It strikes us as very inflammatory.

01:45:15.309 --> 01:45:17.477
Why don't we change it to
<i>Plan 9 From Outer Space?</i>

01:45:20.196 --> 01:45:21.564
That's ridiculous.

01:45:24.235 --> 01:45:26.653
All right. And, action!

01:45:29.740 --> 01:45:32.492
Medical examiner been around yet?

01:45:32.576 --> 01:45:35.954
Just left. The morgue wagon
oughta be along most any time.

01:45:36.038 --> 01:45:39.541
- You get their statement?
- Yeah, but they're pretty scared.

01:45:39.625 --> 01:45:42.002
Fine mess like this
will frighten anyone.

01:45:42.086 --> 01:45:44.004
You have one of the boys

01:45:44.088 --> 01:45:47.340
take the guy and the girl back to town,
you take charge.

01:45:47.425 --> 01:45:50.343
What'd you give him all the lines for?
He's unintelligible.

01:45:50.428 --> 01:45:53.179
Lugosi's dead and Vampira won't talk,
I had to give somebody the dialogue!

01:45:53.264 --> 01:45:55.223
That is no answer!

01:45:56.851 --> 01:45:58.768
What about glitter?

01:45:58.853 --> 01:46:00.687
When I was a headliner in Paris,

01:46:00.771 --> 01:46:02.731
audiences always liked it
when I sparkled.

01:46:02.815 --> 01:46:04.774
No!

01:46:04.859 --> 01:46:06.776
- Cat's eyes!
- No!

01:46:06.861 --> 01:46:08.778
Well, I'm going to need some antennae.

01:46:08.863 --> 01:46:09.904
No!

01:46:10.072 --> 01:46:12.449
You're the ruler of the galaxy!
Show a little taste!

01:46:17.329 --> 01:46:19.539
See? No talking. Isn't he good?

01:46:19.623 --> 01:46:22.542
- Cue Dr. Tom.
- Now?

01:46:22.626 --> 01:46:24.627
Yes, now. Lurk him.

01:46:30.968 --> 01:46:33.595
Be sure and keep your face covered.

01:46:41.604 --> 01:46:44.647
Isn't it wonderful? Bela lives.

01:46:44.732 --> 01:46:47.400
Doesn't it strike you as a bit morbid?

01:46:47.485 --> 01:46:49.402
No. He would've loved it.

01:46:49.487 --> 01:46:51.571
Bela's returned from the grave.

01:46:51.655 --> 01:46:54.074
Just like Dracula. Cue Vampira.

01:47:08.762 --> 01:47:09.714
Cut!

01:47:09.799 --> 01:47:12.801
Let's go down and find out
whose grave it is.

01:47:12.885 --> 01:47:16.054
Oh, why do I always get hooked up
with these spook details?

01:47:16.305 --> 01:47:18.139
Monsters, graves, bodies!

01:47:18.390 --> 01:47:20.183
Cue flying saucer.

01:47:25.064 --> 01:47:27.190
And cut! Print. We're moving on.

01:47:28.818 --> 01:47:31.069
- That was perfect.
- Perfect? Mr. Wood,

01:47:31.153 --> 01:47:34.405
do you know anything
about the art of film production?

01:47:34.490 --> 01:47:36.407
Well, I like to think so.

01:47:36.492 --> 01:47:38.618
That cardboard headstone tipped over.

01:47:38.702 --> 01:47:41.329
This graveyard is obviously phony.

01:47:42.623 --> 01:47:44.624
Nobody will ever notice that.

01:47:44.708 --> 01:47:47.585
Filmmaking is not about the tiny details.
It's about the big picture.

01:47:47.670 --> 01:47:49.295
- The big picture?
- Yes.

01:47:49.380 --> 01:47:53.174
How about when the policemen arrived in daylight,
but now it's suddenly night?

01:47:53.259 --> 01:47:56.136
What do you know?
Haven't you heard of suspension of disbelief?

01:47:56.220 --> 01:47:58.179
Reverend, I'm here.

01:47:59.964 --> 01:48:01.141
Who is he?

01:48:01.225 --> 01:48:03.476
This is our choir director.

01:48:03.561 --> 01:48:06.020
He's gonna play the young hero.

01:48:09.066 --> 01:48:12.110
Are you people insane?
I'm the director!

01:48:12.194 --> 01:48:14.154
I make the casting decisions around here!

01:48:15.239 --> 01:48:17.157
I thought this was a group effort.

01:48:17.241 --> 01:48:19.242
No!

01:48:21.245 --> 01:48:22.745
No?

01:48:22.997 --> 01:48:25.081
They're driving me crazy!

01:48:26.584 --> 01:48:30.879
These Baptists are stupid, stupid, stupid!

01:48:33.090 --> 01:48:36.634
Okay. I gotta calm down.

01:48:36.719 --> 01:48:38.687
Gotta calm down.

01:48:40.973 --> 01:48:43.021
Gotta calm down.

01:48:43.100 --> 01:48:45.059
Take a deep breath.

01:48:45.144 --> 01:48:47.103
Relax.

01:48:52.610 --> 01:48:54.986
All right, everybody.
Let's get set up for scene 112.

01:48:55.070 --> 01:48:58.114
Move the crypt stage left,
and let's get Tor's make-up effect ready.

01:48:59.450 --> 01:49:00.825
Mr. Wood!

01:49:00.910 --> 01:49:04.329
- What do you think you're doing?
- I'm directing.

01:49:04.413 --> 01:49:06.456
Not like that you're not!

01:49:06.540 --> 01:49:08.958
Remove that get-up immediately!

01:49:09.043 --> 01:49:11.044
You shame our Lord.

01:49:15.382 --> 01:49:18.259
That's it! I can't take it!

01:49:25.935 --> 01:49:28.436
Take me to the nearest bar,
and make it snappy!

01:49:38.781 --> 01:49:40.782
Imperial Whiskey.

01:50:00.177 --> 01:50:02.845
Oh, my gosh.

01:50:03.097 --> 01:50:04.847
Orson Welles.

01:50:17.027 --> 01:50:19.404
- Excuse me, sir?
- Yes?

01:50:19.488 --> 01:50:23.700
Um, well, I'm a young filmmaker
and a real big fan.

01:50:23.951 --> 01:50:26.077
I just wanted to meet you.

01:50:27.371 --> 01:50:29.580
My pleasure. I'm Orson Welles.

01:50:29.665 --> 01:50:32.333
I'm, uh, Edward D. Wood, Jr.

01:50:35.004 --> 01:50:37.213
What you working on?

01:50:37.298 --> 01:50:41.009
Well, the financing just fell through
for the third time on <i>Don Quixote.</i>

01:50:41.093 --> 01:50:43.052
You know, I can't believe it.

01:50:43.137 --> 01:50:45.305
That sounds just exactly like my problems.

01:50:45.389 --> 01:50:46.514
It's the damn money men.

01:50:46.890 --> 01:50:49.475
They never know who's a windbag
and who's got the goods.

01:50:49.560 --> 01:50:51.477
Then they all think they're directors.

01:50:51.562 --> 01:50:52.770
Ain't that the truth?

01:50:52.855 --> 01:50:55.231
Do you know that I've even
had producers re-cut my movies?

01:50:55.316 --> 01:50:57.025
I hate when that happens.

01:50:57.109 --> 01:50:58.818
And they're always trying
to cast their buddies.

01:50:58.902 --> 01:51:00.820
It doesn't even matter
if they're right for the part.

01:51:00.904 --> 01:51:04.657
Tell me about it.
I'm supposed to do a thriller at Universal

01:51:04.742 --> 01:51:07.327
but they want Charlton Heston
to play a Mexican.

01:51:10.830 --> 01:51:13.624
Mr. Welles. Is it all worth it?

01:51:13.709 --> 01:51:16.210
It is when it works.

01:51:16.295 --> 01:51:19.589
You know, the one film of mine
where I had total control, <i>Kane?</i>

01:51:19.673 --> 01:51:21.841
The studio hated it

01:51:21.925 --> 01:51:24.761
but they didn't get to touch a frame.

01:51:25.387 --> 01:51:28.598
- Ed.
- Yes?

01:51:28.682 --> 01:51:31.059
Visions are worth fighting for.

01:51:31.143 --> 01:51:34.103
Why spend your life
making someone else's dreams?

01:51:40.444 --> 01:51:43.780
Thank you, Orson.

01:51:47.785 --> 01:51:49.077
- Mr. Reynolds.
- Yes.

01:51:49.161 --> 01:51:51.871
We are gonna finish this picture
just the way I want it

01:51:51.955 --> 01:51:53.873
because you cannot compromise
an artist's vision.

01:51:53.957 --> 01:51:56.167
- But it's our money.
- And you're gonna make a bundle

01:51:56.251 --> 01:51:59.212
but only if you shut up
and let me do things my way.

01:51:59.296 --> 01:52:04.175
All right, gang. Actors in positions.
Let's finish this picture.

01:52:14.144 --> 01:52:15.269
Action.

01:52:25.239 --> 01:52:28.699
Wanna give him a hand?
Keep rolling.

01:52:46.343 --> 01:52:48.261
Now that's an alien.

01:52:49.346 --> 01:52:50.888
Action.

01:52:57.980 --> 01:53:00.690
- What plan will you follow now?
- Plan 9.

01:53:00.774 --> 01:53:03.609
Plan 9? Ah, yes.

01:53:03.694 --> 01:53:07.405
Plan 9 deals with the resurrection of the dead.

01:53:07.656 --> 01:53:11.325
Long-distance electrodes shot into
the pineal and pituitary glands

01:53:11.410 --> 01:53:13.244
of the recent dead.

01:53:13.871 --> 01:53:16.873
You know, maybe you guys were right.
"Plan 9" is a good title.

01:53:17.082 --> 01:53:19.459
I want that lightning,
I want those two explosions

01:53:19.543 --> 01:53:20.793
and I've got to have
more shots of the military!

01:53:20.878 --> 01:53:21.919
Right.

01:53:44.693 --> 01:53:46.319
And cut.

01:53:46.403 --> 01:53:49.405
All right, friends.
Prepare for scene 32.

01:53:49.490 --> 01:53:51.491
- Mr. Wood?
- Yeah?

01:53:51.575 --> 01:53:55.745
- Where's the cockpit set?
- You're standing in it. Places!

01:54:13.472 --> 01:54:15.848
But what if we develop
this solenite bomb?

01:54:15.933 --> 01:54:17.934
Then we'd be a stronger nation, too.

01:54:18.018 --> 01:54:20.186
"Stronger." You see?

01:54:20.270 --> 01:54:23.189
You see? Your stupid minds.

01:54:23.273 --> 01:54:25.191
Stupid. Stupid!

01:54:25.275 --> 01:54:27.276
- That's all I'm gonna take outta you!
- Oh!

01:54:31.240 --> 01:54:32.532
Cut!

01:54:32.616 --> 01:54:34.659
Action.

01:54:41.041 --> 01:54:43.209
Greetings, my friend.

01:54:43.293 --> 01:54:45.253
We are all interested in the future

01:54:45.337 --> 01:54:50.299
for that is where you and I are going
to spend the rest of our lives.

01:54:50.384 --> 01:54:52.343
And remember, my friend,

01:54:52.427 --> 01:54:56.597
future events such as these
will affect you in the future.

01:55:14.324 --> 01:55:16.492
And cut!

01:55:17.661 --> 01:55:19.328
That's a wrap.

01:55:36.346 --> 01:55:37.513
Oh!

01:55:44.354 --> 01:55:46.272
I can't get it up. It's stuck.

01:55:46.356 --> 01:55:49.317
Eddie, you're gonna be late
for your own premiere.

01:55:49.401 --> 01:55:51.360
All right, forget it.

01:55:55.866 --> 01:55:57.867
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,</i>

01:55:57.951 --> 01:56:00.536
<i>you are about to see
an extraordinary motion picture.</i>

01:56:00.787 --> 01:56:04.999
<i>But before it begins,
I think we should all give a hand to the man</i>

01:56:05.083 --> 01:56:08.461
<i>without whom we wouldn't
be here tonight.</i>

01:56:08.545 --> 01:56:10.504
<i>Eddie, take a bow!</i>

01:56:49.002 --> 01:56:51.337
<i>Thank you.</i>

01:56:51.421 --> 01:56:54.632
<i>I just wanna say that this film</i>

01:56:55.717 --> 01:56:57.635
<i>is for Bela.</i>

01:57:47.602 --> 01:57:49.562
<i>The grief of his wife's death</i>

01:57:49.646 --> 01:57:52.606
<i>became greater and greater agony.</i>

01:57:54.401 --> 01:57:58.070
<i>The home they had so long shared together</i>

01:57:58.155 --> 01:58:00.281
<i>became a tomb.</i>

01:58:00.365 --> 01:58:03.826
<i>A sweet memory of her joyous living.</i>

01:58:05.370 --> 01:58:08.330
<i>The sky to which he had once looked</i>

01:58:08.415 --> 01:58:11.584
<i>was now only a covering
for her dead body.</i>

01:58:19.760 --> 01:58:23.763
<i>The ever-beautiful flowers
she had planted</i>

01:58:23.847 --> 01:58:25.765
<i>with her own hands</i>

01:58:25.849 --> 01:58:30.144
<i>became nothing more than
the lost roses of her cheeks.</i>

01:58:33.523 --> 01:58:35.691
<i>Confused by his great loss,</i>

01:58:35.776 --> 01:58:38.319
<i>the old man left that home</i>

01:58:38.403 --> 01:58:40.738
<i>never to return again.</i>

01:58:56.129 --> 01:58:58.172
This is the one.

01:58:58.256 --> 01:59:01.050
This is the one I'll be remembered for.

01:59:05.722 --> 01:59:08.641
Aw, gee, honey, I'm so happy for ya!

01:59:08.725 --> 01:59:10.893
Say, let's get married.

01:59:11.228 --> 01:59:13.687
- Huh?
- Right now. Let's go to Vegas.

01:59:13.772 --> 01:59:16.440
But, Eddie, it's pouring,
and the car top is stuck.

01:59:16.525 --> 01:59:18.275
Phooey! It's only a five-hour drive

01:59:18.360 --> 01:59:20.110
and it'll probably stop
by the time we get to the desert.

01:59:20.529 --> 01:59:24.240
Heck, it'll probably stop by the time
we get around the corner. Let's go.

01:59:26.576 --> 01:59:27.428
Oh!

